<div id="map"></div>
```

- In your JavaScript code, initialize the map by calling the `google.maps.Map` constructor, passing the container element and any desired options:
````javascript
var map = new google.maps.Map(document.getElementById('map'), {
    center: { lat: YOUR_LATITUDE, lng: YOUR_LONGITUDE },
    zoom: INITIAL_ZOOM_LEVEL
});
```
Replace `YOUR_LATITUDE` and `YOUR_LONGITUDE` with the desired initial map center coordinates and `INITIAL_ZOOM_LEVEL` with the desired zoom level.
